{
  "texts": [
    "Firstly, there is a need for a welldesigned LLM4DB architecture that supports common database functionalities.",
    "For instance, a comprehensive LLM can be designed to forecast and schedule workloads across different components, with each component or function is driven by a fine-tuned LLM.",
    "Additionally, it is crucial to improve the efficiency of model inference.",
    "This requires the model to generate reasonable predictions or decisions without excessively consuming system resources.",
    "Some potential approaches include distilling the model into smaller models and supporting concurrent model inferences."
  ]
}